ickets from the Office of the Chief of Staff  These tickets will be handed out the week of 25 through 29 April  For cadets requesting additional tickets  it is recommended that they first ask their Class Officers for any unused tickets  This is the most effective way of identifying unused tickets and redistributing them  The Class of 2016 Class Officers will arrange an  excess ticket turn in  system  Additionally  there will be a ticket turn in and pick up booth outside of Cameron Hall the morning of graduation  Family members who do not use all of their tickets may turn them in and those who need additional tickets may get them on a first come  first served basis  there will be a booth where families general turn in extra tickets  but we can not guarantee there will be availability  Do children need a ticket  Answer Children 3 and over will need a ticket  Cameron Hall is a basketball stadium and there is limited room for strollers  Strollers can not be kept inside the access portals leading into the area due to fire code  If you feel the need to bring one they will need to be folded and kept in the hallway  VMI will not be responsible for unattended strollers and items  Is Commencement open to the public  Answer Commencement Ceremonies in Cameron Hall are restricted to guests of the graduating class  However  the simulcast viewing of the event in Marshall Hall  Gillis Theater  is open to the public  If you have family and friends that will be unable to attend the events in person  they may be able to view the ceremonies of the VMI Commissioning Ceremony and the VMI Commencement ceremony via life streaming at it will be broadcast at www vmi edu livestream  Which events are open to the public  All events are open to the public  except the Superintendent s Reception and Commencement  Limited seating is available for many of the events so we encourage guests to arrive early  For additional information  please contact the Chief of Staff s office at  540  464 7104  Handicapped seating and access  Answer Handicapped seating is available for commencement events  A reserved area for persons with a walking disability or those using a wheelchair is available  Due to the large number attending and the limited space  seating is available for the person who needs the special seating and one accompanying guest or attendant  No individuals will be permitted down in the specialized seating area in Cameron Hall unless they are on the list Please contact Katrina Butner at butnerkk vmi edu in the Office of the Chief of Staff to make the necessary arrangements  All guests using wheelchairs must enter Cameron Hall through the front entrance and will be escorted to the designated handicap seating area  Please let us know of your needs as far in advance as possible  We can not guarantee special seating requests made 72 hours prior to the ceremony  There are designated handicap parking slots across Post but please advise your family members and guests that parking is limited and it is available on a first come  first served basis so please plan arrival times accordingly  Guests needing assistance should bring their own or rented wheelchairs or walkers since these  or other devices are not provided by VMI  What should I wear   Answer Casual business attire is appropriate for all events  Refreshments for the public  Refreshments are available in the Keydet Kanteen located in Lejeune Hall   Third Barracks  There will also be refreshments outside of Cameron Hall on the morning of graduation for a fee  Are there public restrooms  Answer Restrooms are located in J M  Hall  Preston Library  Cameron Hall and Lejeune Hall located at the end of Third Barracks  Where do I order graduation photos  Graduation photos can be purchased from Candid Color Photography approximately ten days after graduation  Please visit their website at www candidcolor net  Please enter access code VMIG16  You may also call 1 800 321 4256  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Commencement FAQs  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu May Graduation Institute Awards Commissioning New Market Ceremony Graduation 2016 Ceremony Sen  Tim Kaine to Speak FAQs Media Resources Parking Info December G